name: Court of Appeal
description: Second highest court in Ghana, handles appeals from High Courts
jurisdiction: Appeals from High Courts and Circuit Courts
presiding_judge: President of the Court of Appeal

name: High Court
description: Superior court of record with unlimited jurisdiction
jurisdiction: Civil and criminal matters, constitutional issues
presiding_judge: Chief Judge of the High Court

name: Circuit Court
description: Intermediate court handling serious criminal and civil cases
jurisdiction: Serious criminal offences and civil cases up to specified amounts

name: District Court
description: Lower court handling minor criminal and civil matters
jurisdiction: Minor criminal offences and civil cases

name: Magistrate Court
description: Lowest court in the hierarchy handling petty cases
jurisdiction: Petty criminal offences and small civil claims

name: High Court Kumasi
description: High Court serving the Ashanti Region
jurisdiction: Civil and criminal matters in Ashanti Region

name: Circuit Court Tamale
description: Circuit Court serving the Northern Region
jurisdiction: Serious criminal and civil cases in Northern Region

name: District Court Takoradi
description: District Court serving the Western Region
jurisdiction: Minor criminal and civil matters in Western Region

name: Commercial Court
description: Specialized High Court handling commercial disputes
jurisdiction: Commercial disputes, contract matters, business litigation
